  "prompt": "Are you even really dating someone if you see them once per week for just a few hours?",
  "response": "The definition of dating can vary widely depending on the individuals involved and their expectations. For some, seeing someone once a week for a few hours may be sufficient for a meaningful connection, especially if both people are content with that arrangement. For others, they might feel that more frequent interactions are necessary to establish a deeper relationship. \n\nCommunication is key\u2014discussing your feelings, intentions, and expectations with your partner can help clarify what dating means for both of you. If both individuals are on the same page and enjoy the time they spend together, then that can certainly be considered dating. Ultimately, it's about the quality of the connection rather than just the quantity of time spent together.",
